In an episode of Oprah: Where Are They Now? airing on Sunday night their parents talked about what it was like raising such a large brood.

Meals are served buffet style and 15 to 17 loads of laundry get done per week.

Family matriarch, Bobbi, 46, said that food shopping remains one of the biggest struggles and she buys everything in bulk in a bid to cut costs.

She recently snapped up 60lbs of hamburgers after spotting them on sale at a local grocery store and she grows fresh produce in the garden. 

